title: RocketLab Updates Neutron Design
summary: RocketLab has released new renders of their Neutron rocket. Rocket Lab's Neutron rocket, is a cutting-edge medium-lift two-stage launch vehicle currently in development.

title: Investing in Space: What to watch for in Q2 earnings reports
summary: As Wall Street works its way through second-quarter earnings reports, investors are getting a closer look at first-half performance from the space sector — and setting expectations for the second half of the year.

title: Northrop Grumman takes $36 million charge on NASA Gateway module
summary: Northrop Grumman said it took a $36 million charge on its contract to build a module for NASA’s lunar Gateway, citing changing mission requirements and broader economic issues.

title: Pair of Chinese launches put flat-panel satellite, new spy sats in orbit
